      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for NIH at all 5 operating points using validation metric (E = (M - D)/D × 100%). Mean |E| = 8.3%, maximum |E| = 14.1% (within U95 = 12.4% combined uncertainty). Comparison metric accounts for both experimental and numerical uncertainty. Systematic bias assessed; no statistically significant trend identified (p = 0.31 via Spearman rank correlation with flow rate).",
