      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which is the regulatory-accepted metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per ASTM F1841. NIH directly maps to the COU decision criterion (relative hemolysis index RH < 1). Secondary QoI (pump head) is mechanistically linked to hemolysis generation. Both QoIs are directly observable and measurable in the validation experiment.",
